definition: to be unsure about a matter/to be uncertain/to be unable to make sense of sth
variant of 吃[chi1]
to eat/to consume/to eat at (a cafeteria etc)/to eradicate/to destroy/to absorb/to suffer/to stammer (Taiwan pr. for this sense is [ji2])
(negative prefix)/not/no
to allow/to grant/in accordance with/in the light of
accurate/standard/definitely/certainly/about to become (bride, son-in-law etc)/quasi-/para-

sentences.english: A. Everybody is not sure when she'll finally come.
sentences.chinese: 她最终什么时候来，大家都吃不准。

sentences.english: I'm not sure what time you can reach him.
sentences.chinese: 我吃不准你什么时候可以打电话找到他。

sentences.english: Have laber or steak?I am not sure.
sentences.chinese: 点龙虾呢还是要牛排呢，我吃不准。

sentences.english: There is some doubt about the best way to do it.
sentences.chinese: 这件事怎么做才是最佳办法有点吃不准。

sentences.english: You'd better consult the exposure meter if you're not sure of the time for exposure.
sentences.chinese: 如果你吃不准曝光时间，最好查一下曝光表。

sentences.english: She was not sure she had heard him, and was about to repeat the question.
sentences.chinese: 她吃不准自己是否听清了他的话，正准备再问一遍。

sentences.english: I am not sure how he will react to such a straightforward answer.
sentences.chinese: 我吃不准他会对如此直率的回答作出什么反应。

sentences.english: They were unsure of who was to blame.
Not sure on the development of future Mars text into the text of a comet.
sentences.chinese: 吃不准火星文今后就发展成彗星文了。

unsure/uncertain/unending

to be confused/to be baffled
restless/apprehensive
